---
title: Vegan One-Pan BBQ Bean & Coleslaw Wraps with Tortilla Chips & Guac
description: Craving all the tantalizing flavors and textures of a burrito—minus the meat? Look no further, this fresh, filling lunch comes together in just 15 minutes! For this Tex-Mex-inspired vegan dish, you’ll slather tortillas with spicy vegan mayo, then layer on warm, hearty BBQ red beans and crisp, tangy coleslaw with scallions. Serve with blue corn chips and creamy guacamole on the side for dipping to your heart’s content.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6488872e28c9744b12dcdc76-d989d742.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6488872e28c9744b12dcdc76.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Southwest
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 122 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 1610 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-bbq-bean-coleslaw-wraps-6488872e28c9744b12dcdc76
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%units}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} and half the @vegan mayo{2%tablespoon}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, scallions, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, remaining mayonnaise, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; set aside.

> Use 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Drain @kidney beans{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add drained beans, @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until beans are warmed through and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Use 2 TBSP water for 4 servings.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Evenly spread spicy mayo on bottom third of tortillas. Top with BBQ beans and as much coleslaw as you like. Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Divide wraps between #plates{}. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce}, @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, and any remaining coleslaw on the side.